<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>Just wondering if TheBlack even plays PVP</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?Ellos">Ellos</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 11:48 a.m. 28/6/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Just wondering if TheBlack even plays PVP<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR></STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>Now I been looking at message boards for the last hour or so.. and it did not take me long to find another person... In addition to the people that already responeded about pvp exp loss here.. here let me quote him so you can see yourself.

<P>4.) Any angry, sick, or plain-old-bored caster with a DoT has within his power to slay you and make you lose experience. Even worse, is the fact that because they died of "natural" causes, the DoT-slinging caster does not take a faction hit from the new PVP faction system. (I'd also like to point out that this new faction system is worthless for half-elves because there is no half-elf city and I have yet to see a powerful half-elf NPC, other than the few in High Hold Pass, that it would affect.)
<P>Let me point out that this was on the Everquest.com message board under Rallos Zek (PvP) posted by oxidatiOn if you want to go see it for yourself.. So as far as anyone "important" is concerend they are just ignoring the pvp community!!!
<BR>
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
